Package: glemb
Title: Multiple Imputation Using the General Location Model with the EMB Algorithm
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Paul", "Allison", email = "allison@statisticalhorizons.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides multiple imputation for mixed continuous and categorical
    data using the General Location Model (Olkin & Tate 1961; Little &
    Schluchter 1987) combined with the Expectation-Maximization with
    Bootstrapping (EMB) algorithm. Factor variables are automatically treated
    as categorical; all other variables are treated as continuous. The package
    wraps the EM implementation in the 'mix' package and extends it with a
    bootstrap wrapper to produce proper multiple imputations in the sense of
    Rubin (1987).
